title: Eddie Money Greatest Hits
description: Eddie Money was always reliable for turning out a hit single or radio anthem on each of his records. Often, it felt like all of his energy went into a couple of songs per album, since the remainder of each record, while frequently enjoyable, was cluttered with filler. Which is a roundabout way of saying what a welcome addition Greatest Hits: The Sound of Money is to Money&#039;s catalog: not only is it a fine collection of his hits, it&#039;s the most consistent record he&#039;s assembled. Not that it&#039;s perfect. Some of his smaller hits are missing and there&#039;s a bit of filler even on this hits disc, but the truly essential items -- "Baby Hold On," "Two Tickets to Paradise," "I Wanna Go Back," "Walk on Water," "Shakin&#039;," "Take Me Home Tonight," "Think I&#039;m in Love," even "Peace in Our Time" -- are here, and the best of them really do define what album-rock was all about at the turn of the &#039;70s and early &#039;80s. ~ Stephen Thomas Erlewine, All Music Guide
